This is Yog vesrion 0.0.9
=========================

Yog is a dynamic programming language designed as an intermediate between Pythonand Ruby.

Features
--------

* Syntax like Python and Ruby
* Object Oriented
  * Class based
* Garbage Collection
* The MIT License

Requirements
------------

* CPU
  * Intel x86
* OS
  * Ubuntu Linux 8.04
  * FreeBSD 8.1
  * OpenBSD 4.6

Documentation
-------------

Online documents are at http://SumiTomohiko.github.com/Yog/.

Offline documents are available in the ``doc/html`` directory.

Download
--------

See

* http://github.com/SumiTomohiko/Yog/downloads

Build Instructions
------------------

See ``INSTALL``.

Issue Tracking System
---------------------

You can see the issues at http://neko-daisuki.ddo.jp/~SumiTomohiko/yog/issues/index.html.
Original data are in the ``issues`` dicretory of the source tree.

Development progress & plans
----------------------------

by version 0.0.2 (done)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* Port to Windows 2000. (Cancelled at 0.0.7)
* Port to OpenBSD.
* Port to FreeBSD.

by version 0.0.3 (done)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* Coroutine.

by version 0.0.4 (done)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* Bugfix

by version 0.0.5 (done)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* Generational GC

by version 0.0.6 (done)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* libffi binding

by version 0.0.7 (done)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* Performance tuning

by version 0.0.8 (done)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* Change internal encoding of strings to UTF-32

by version 0.0.9 (done)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* Improved the regular expression faster by using corgi.
  * http://github.com/SumiTomohiko/corgi

by version 1.0.0
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* Stabilize.

by version 42
~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* Become a cartoon film.

